                            <comment id="13973" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 19 Jul 2005 22:29:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve refined JdbcUtils.getResultSetValue to detect a Blob or Clob object returned by ResultSet.getObject, explicitly calling ResultSet.getBytes respectively ResultSet.getString in that case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will return detached object values (not depending on the active ResultSet) even when no required type has been specified on SingleColumnRowMapper.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
